========== Passives =====
Damage Resistances: lightning, necrotic, piercing
Damage Immunities: cold, fire, poison
Condition Immunities: charmed, frightened, paralyzed, poisoned
Illumination: The flameskull sheds either dim light in a 15-ft radius, or bright light in a 15-ft radius and dim light for an additional 15 ft. It can switch between teh options as an action
Magic Resistance: The flameskull has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects
Rejuvenation: If the flameskull is destroyed, it regains all its hit points in 1 hour unless holy water is sprinkled on its remains or a dispel magic or remove curse spell is cast on them
Spellcasting: The flameskull is a 5th level spellcaster. Its spellcasting ability is Intelligence (spell save DC 13, +5 to hit with spell attacks). It requires no somatic or material components to cast its spells. The flameskull has the following wizard spells prepared: Cantrip: mage hand 1st level (3 slots): magic missile, shield 2nd level (2 slots): blur, flaming sphere 3rd level (1 slot): fireball
